org.lisoft.gonector

Class GoTextProtocol

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.lisoft.gonector.GoTextProtocol
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.concurrent.Callable<java.lang.Void>

    public class GoTextProtocol
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.concurrent.Callable<java.lang.Void>
    This class implements the GTP protocol and links it to a GoEngine. The class implements Callable so that you can submit it to an ExecutorService to run asynchronously.

    • Constructor Detail

      • GoTextProtocol

        public GoTextProtocol(java.io.BufferedReader aReader,
                      java.io.Writer aWriter,
                      GoEngine aEngine)
        Creates a new GoTextProtocol instance.
        Parameters:
        aReader - The reader to read input from the controller from. It is the responsibility of the caller to close this reader when call() exits.
        aWriter - A writer to send input to the controller from. It is the responsibility of the caller to close this writer when call() exits.
        aEngine - A GoEngine that is used for serving the requests from the controller.

    • Method Detail

      • call

        public java.lang.Void call()
                    throws java.lang.Exception
        Runs the protocol until the remote disconnects.
        Specified by:
        call in interface java.util.concurrent.Callable<java.lang.Void>
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Whatever the GoEngine throws. If GoEngine throws this method will log the error and then re-throw, terminating the parsing. The connection to the controller must then be reset because the engine and the controller may have de-synced.
